TITLE: Fetching Advertiser Transaction Records via TikTok Business API in Python
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to retrieve transaction records for an advertiser account using the advertiser_transaction_get method from the TikTok Business API client. It requires an integer bc_id, an authorized access token, and optional parameters like filtering criteria, page number, and page size for pagination. The response contains transaction data encapsulated in an InlineResponse200 object. Errors during the API call are caught and printed using the ApiException class.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tiktok/tiktok-business-api-sdk/blob/main/python_sdk/docs/BcPaymentApi.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
from __future__ import print_function
import time
import business_api_client
from business_api_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

# create an instance of the API class
api_instance = business_api_client.BcPaymentApi()
bc_id = 789 # int | 
access_token = 'access_token_example' # str | Authorized access token. For details, see https://ads.tiktok.com/marketing_api/docs?id=1738373164380162.
filtering = None # object |  (optional)
page = 1 # int |  (optional) (default to 1)
page_size = 10 # int |  (optional) (default to 10)

try:
    # Get transaction records of an ad account. BcPayment Advertiser Transaction Get
    api_response = api_instance.advertiser_transaction_get(bc_id, access_token, filtering=filtering, page=page, page_size=page_size)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling BcPaymentApi->advertiser_transaction_get: %s\n" % e)
```

